Step 1: Install Docker
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y docker.io
sudo systemctl start docker
sudo systemctl enable docker
 Step 2: Run MinIO Container
docker run -p 9000:9000 -p 9001:9001 --name minio \
 -e "MINIO_ROOT_USER=minioadmin" \
 -e "MINIO_ROOT_PASSWORD=minioadmin" \
 -v /mnt/data:/data \
 -d minio/minio server /data --console-address ":9001"
 Step 3: Access Web Console

Open browser:

http://<VM-IP>:9001

Login:

Username: minioadmin
Password: minioadmin

 You’ll see:

Buckets
Object browser
Upload UI
 PART 2: mc (MinIO Client)
 Install mc
wget https://dl.min.io/client/mc/release/linux-amd64/mc
chmod +x mc
sudo mv mc /usr/local/bin/
 Configure Alias
mc alias set local http://127.0.0.1:9000 minioadmin minioadmin
 Bucket Operations
Create bucket
mc mb local/mybucket
Upload file
echo "Hello MinIO" > file.txt
mc cp file.txt local/mybucket
List objects
mc ls local/mybucket
 PART 3: S3 API (AWS CLI)

Install AWS CLI:

sudo apt install -y awscli
Configure
aws configure

Use:

Access Key: minioadmin
Secret Key: minioadmin
Region: us-east-1
Test S3 API
aws --endpoint-url http://127.0.0.1:9000 s3 ls

 You should see your bucket:

mybucket
📤 Upload via S3 API
aws --endpoint-url http://127.0.0.1:9000 s3 cp file.txt s3://mybucket/
